<HEADLINE> France Hands Over First Airbus Plane to Air China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, October 7 (Xinhua) -- France today handed over the first
Airbus A340 passenger plane to Air China at the headquarters of
the Aerospatiale airspace consortium in Toulouse, southern France.
</P>
<P>
Air China has ordered three planes of this type and will
receive the two others by the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
The planes will be flown between Beijing and some European
capitals, including Paris, London and Rome. 
</P>
</TEXT>
