<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mongolia to Get New Aid Worth $250 Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, October 7 (Xinhua) -- A group of countries and
international organizations pledged here today to provide Mongolia
with some 250 million U.S. dollars of new aid next year to support
the country's bid to create a market economy.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made at the 6th Mongolian Assistance Group
Meeting, which ended in Tokyo today.
</P>
<P>
Co-sponsored by the Japanese government and the World Bank, the
meeting was attended by 20 countries and six international
organizations.
</P>
<P>
The participants also agreed to hold the next session within 18
months in Ulan Bator, the capital of Mongolia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
