<HEADLINE> AT&AMP;T Looking for Partner </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, October 7 (Xinhua) -- AT&AMP;T, the No. 1
telecommunication company in the U.S., is looking for a partner,
under the pressure of WorldCom's bid for MCI, U.S. newspapers
reported today.
</P>
<P>
Last week, the WorldCom, the fourth largest telecommunication
company, offered to buy MCI, the second largest, with 30 billion
U.S. dollars. The combination, if made possible, would create a
threat to AT&AMP;T and also intensify market competition.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, At&AMP;T is in talks with several
companies, including GTE.
</P>
<P>
The report said that AT&AMP;T is trying to find an alliance that
would ensure its dominance in telecommunications. Other possible
partners include Sprint, U.S. West, Teleport Communications Group
and Intermedia. But all of these declined to comment.
</P>
<P>
GTE has a local phone business in 28 states and a new
long-distance unit that has won 1 million customers. GTE has a
close relationship with AT&AMP;T, it was reported, and its chief
executive, Chuck Lee, could also succeed Bob Allen at AT&AMP;T.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971008.0008 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Stock Exchange To Play Active Role in China's Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 7 (Xinhua) -- The Stock Exchange of Hong
Kong will perform a uniquely important role in the economic
development of China, Financial Secretary of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR) Donald Tsang said here today.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a reception to mark the stock exchange's 11th
anniversary, Tsang said that in addition to playing a pivotal role
in the international financial market, the stock exchange has
also become the most important fund raising center for
enterprises from China's interior areas.
</P>
<P>
He quoted Chairman Edgar Cheng of the stock exchange as saying
a few days ago that with the liquidity and robust infrastructure
of the market, Hong Kong can play a leading role as the primary
market for inland companies to access international capital.
</P>
<P>
Tsang described a seminar held two months ago in Chengdu,
southwest China, to introduce the capital raising opportunities in
Hong Kong as a "big success."
</P>
<P>
The seminar, jointly organized by the stock exchange, the
Securities and Futures Commission and the Trade Development
Council, was attended by more than 300 officials, entrepreneurs
and market professionals from China's inland areas.
</P>
<P>
The financial secretary spoke highly of what the stock exchange
has achieved this year, which he described as a "remarkable" year
in its history.
</P>
<P>
As at the end of July, the stock exchange was rated the sixth
largest exchange in the world with a total market capitalization
of over 4.3 trillion HK dollars (550 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The increase in market capitalization was almost 60 percent
over the previous year, which is the highest among the major
exchanges all around the world, Tsang said.
</P>
<P>
The stock exchange also dedicates itself to providing investors
with the best and most professional services, he added. "Your
achievement in this respect has been obvious. The way our market
has met the challenges and volatility provoked by the currency
crisis in our neighboring markets in the last couple of months
speaks for itself," he noted.
</P>
<P>
Tsang also commended the stock exchange's efforts in developing
new financial products and markets and educating investors.
</P>
<P>
in his speech, Edgar Cheng, who will be stepping down soon from
the chairmanship of the stock exchange after three years in the
position, pledged that the stock exchange will continue to support
the transformation of the economy and infrastructure in China's
interior areas.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference this afternoon, Chief Executive Alec Tsui
of the stock exchange revealed that the stock exchange had an
average daily turnover of 16.37 billion HK dollars (2.1 billion
U.S. dollars) for the first three quarters of this year, 238
percent higher over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
And the stock exchange is making steps to double the current
trading capacity to 100 billion HK dollars (12.8 billion
U.S. dollars), he said.
</P>
<P>
It is also considering setting up a second-board market for
small and medium-sized companies as a recent survey showed
profound interest in such a market.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng Index, the barometer of the stock exchange, rose
26 percent from 11,902 points in September 1996 to 15,049 points
in September this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971008.0009 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. Africa, India Sign Three Cooperation Accords </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, October 7 (Xinhua) -- South Africa and India today
signed three cooperation agreements in geology and mineral resources,
tourism, and science and technology, South African media
reported.
</P>
<P>
South African President Nelson Mandela and Indian Prime Minister
Inder Kumar Gujral presided over the signing ceremony in Cape Town.
</P>
<P>
Under the tourism agreement, the two governments will establish
tourist offices in each other's countries, reports said.
</P>
<P>
Both countries are eager to boost their tourist industries.
</P>
<P>
Mandela said at the end of September that the contribution of
tourism to South Africa's economy could be doubled from its present
4.5 percent and it had a potential to create hundreds of thousands of
jobs.
</P>
<P>
South African Tourism Minister Pallo Jordan said that tourism could
generate 40 billion Rand (8.5 billion U.S. dollars) annually and
create 2 million jobs if its contribution to the GDP were raised to 10
percent.
</P>
<P>
India is no less enthusiastic in this aspect.
</P>
<P>
The Indian government has been developing tourism in an organized
manner since 1992 and has an ambitious program to develop tourism
through the use of incentives and the building of tourist-related
infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
The two countries are also trying to cooperate in the field of
defense, including the joint development of weapons.
</P>
<P>
The accords signed today were seen as part of the Indo-South
African "strategic partnership" formalized in the Red Fort Declaration
signed by Mandela and then Indian prime minister Deve Gowda in
March, said the reports.
</P>
<P>
The two countries are leading the Indian Ocean Rim Alliance for
Regional Cooperation and both are members of the Non-Aligned Movement
(NAM).
</P>
<P>
Mandela said after talks with Gujral that the two countries were
members of many world bodies and should cooperate and speak with one
voice in these forums.
</P>
<P>
Gujral, who is in South Africa for a visit, is scheduled to address
South African parliament this afternoon, and later he will attend a
banquet in honor of him hosted by Mandela.
</P>
<P>
Gujral's visit to South Africa, the first by an Indian prime
minister, was given special significance because this year is the 50th
anniversary of India's indenpendence.
</P>
<P>
Bilateral relations developed quickly after India lifted sanctions
against former South Africa's all-white government in 1993.
</P>
<P>
Bilateral trade grew to more than 600 million dollars in 1996 from
1993's 80 million.
</P>
<P>
Gujral said Monday that trade between the two countries could reach
2 billion dollars by the end of the century. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971008.0010 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China To Issue "Temple of Heaven" Stamps </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 7 (Xinhua) -- China's Ministry of Posts and
Telecommunications will issue a special Temple of Heaven stamp set
on October 16 this year.
</P>
<P>
The set will include four structures in the Temple of Heaven --
the Hall of Prayer for Good Harvests, Imperial Vault of Heaven,
Circular Mound and Hall of Fasting.
</P>
<P>
The temple, built in 1420 during the Ming Dynasty, was used as
the sacrificial altar where emperors prayed for good harvests. The
temple is the world's largest architectural complex of its kind.
</P>
<P>
The Temple of Heaven covers 273 ha, or four times the area of
the Forbidden City.
</P>
<P>
The set of special stamps is designed by Wang Hufei, a famous
stamp designer, and Ma Gang, an associate professor from the
Central Academy of Fine Arts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971008.0011 </DOCNO>
