<HEADLINE> DRC Business Delegation in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, October 7 (Xinhua) -- A high-powered business
delegation from the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC) is in
Zimbabwe on a trade and investment mission.
</P>
<P>
Native Investments Africa Group, a consortium of Zimbabwe's
indigenous business people which is hosting the Congolese
delegation, said in a statement today the two sides will sign a
government to government commercial agreement which is set to
open up trade between the two countries and is ready for the
signing of a 15 million U.S. Dollars line of credit.
</P>
<P>
The Congolese, who arrived on Sunday and will leave on Friday,
are also expected to secure supplies of various goods and
services and to identify potential partners in the economic
development of their country ravaged by several years of plunder
by former president Mobutu Sese Seko.
</P>
<P>
"There are plenty of advantages for Zimbabwe, from foreign
exchange earnings, employment creation, technology transfer,
barter to culture," said President of Native Investments Africa
Group Philip Chiyangwa.
</P>
<P>
With a population of 46 million people, mineral-rich DRC,
formerly Zaire, requires various forms of assistance from the
international community, said Chiyangwa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
