<DOCNO> XIE19971008.0034 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Uganda's 5th International Trade Fair Unveiled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Uganda's Fifth International
Trade Fair opened today at Lugogo show ground here in the
capital, attracting hundreds of businessmen from over 20
countries all over the world.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the opening of the 7-day fair today, Muganwa
Kaywa, Minister of Trade and Industry said his government has
consistently pursued an economic stability strategy leading to
low inflation, exchange rate stability and increased public and
private sector investments in Uganda.
</P>
<P>
In addition, he said, the government has made substantial
investments in the modernization of the infrastructure in order
to make the economy more competitive.
</P>
<P>
Uganda enjoys peace, stability and an enabling economic
environment, said Kaywa, adding that he hoped foreign countries'
participation in the fair will lead to further promotion and
consolidation of international trade and business exchange with
his country.
</P>
<P>
The current fair has been the fifth and largest trade fair
organized by the Uganda Manufacturers' Association (UMA) since
1993, with the aim of promoting business and developing national
economy.
</P>
<P>
The trade fair which will last until October 12 have attracted
over 320 exhibitors from 21 countries and regions. It is the
first time for France, Germany, Malaysia and Canada to
participate in the fair.
</P>
<P>
The fair is expected to draw over 150,000 people, a fair
source said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
