<HEADLINE> EU Closes Doors on Turkey's Membership: FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Turkish Foreign Minister Ismail
Cem has said that the European Union (EU) has suspended its
consideration for the time being Turkey's membership issue, the
Anatolia News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
Cem made the remarks in the latest edition of Gorus, a
major business magzine in Turkey, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
Despite Turkey's years of efforts for full EU membership, the
European bloc has stopped considering Turkey's bid, the Turkish
foreign minister said.
</P>
<P>
However, he stressed that Turkey, as a part of Europe,
shared the culture of Europe and had the right to be
admitted into the European body.
</P>
<P>
Cem said that the EU should not reject Turkey's efforts
on the grounds of the country's current weakness, adding these
weakness could be overcome step by step.
</P>
<P>
Ankara has been sparing no efforts for a full EU membership
over the past years, but made little progress due to a number of
issues, including the Kurdish problem, human rights as well as
weak economy.
</P>
<P>
The EU's recent decision to hold accession talks with the
Cypriot government also angered Turkey, which provides political,
economic and military support for Turkish Cypriots.
</P>
<P>
Turkish Prime Minister Mesut Yilmaz discussed Turkey's EU
membership issue with German Chancellor Helmut Kohl during his
official visit to Bonn last week.
</P>
<P>
Kohl told Yilmaz that Germany would support Turkey's
membership drive but Ankara should improve its human rights
record and economy first. 
</P>
</TEXT>
