<HEADLINE> Canada Resumes Visa Requirement for Czech Tourists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Canada has resumed visa
requirement for Czech tourists following a surge in refugees
claims, local reports said today.
</P>
<P>
Immigration Minister Lucienne Robillard made public the
decision today, which will take effect on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The latest move comes as a result of rising refugee claimants,
many of them gypsies, from the eastern European country.
</P>
<P>
Czech gypsies began to flood into Canada after a Czech
television show in August, which said there were little racial
discrimination against gypsies and benefits are easy to get in
Canada.
</P>
<P>
During August and September, Canada's immigration department
handled more than 600 Czech refugee claims, three times the number
it handled for all of 1996. 
</P>
