<HEADLINE> Forum to Discuss Guidelines of Party Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Scholars of social sciences in
the capital gathered at a forum here today to exchange their views
on the guidelines of the 15th CPC National Congress.
</P>
<P>
They shared the common view that the banner of Deng Xiaoping
Theory is the soul of the 15th Party Congress and upholding the
banner will guarantee China to realize its cross-century
development goals.
</P>
<P>
Ru Xin, a research fellow with China Academy of Social
Sciences, said that in obtaining a thorough understanding of the
guidelines of the Party congress, theoreticians need to study and
comprehend Deng Xiaoping Theory's historical position and guiding
significance expounded in Jiang Zemin's report to the congress.
</P>
<P>
They agreed that China's being at the primary stage of
socialism is the corner stone of Deng Xiaoping Theory and that
the Party reexaming the theory in Jiang's report has theoretical
and practical importance.
</P>
<P>
"Proceeding from this theory, we can conclude that China stays
now and will remain to be in a long time to come in the primary
stage of socialism," said renowned historian Liu Danian.
</P>
<P>
Liu Yunshan, deputy head of the Propaganda Department of the
CPC Central Committee, called the scholars and experts to further
emancipate their mind, carry on the fine tradition of seeking
truth from facts and play a more active role in promoting the
socialist modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
Today's forum was co-organized by the People's Daily and
Qiushi, the Party's leading journal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
