<HEADLINE> Non-Communist Party Set To Hold National Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 8 (Xinhua) -- The 11th National Congress of
the China Zhi Gong Party (Public Interest Party), one of the major
non-communist parties in China, will open in the Chinese capital
on November 1.
</P>
<P>
The congress will summarize the work of the Zhi Gong Party over
the past 19 years since the adoption of China's reform and opening
policies, with particular emphasis on the past five years. The
congress will also introduce working policies and tasks for the
next five years, according to plans outlined during the 16th
session of the Standing Committee of the 10th Central Committee of
the Party, which closed today.
</P>
<P>
The party's constitution will be revised and a new central
leadership will be elected.
</P>
<P>
The main tasks for the two-day session centered on studying
documents of the 15 National Congress of the Communist Party of
China (CPC), and matters concerning the convocation of the 11th
National Congress of the Zhi Gong Party.
</P>
<P>
Participants attending today's standing committee session
voiced their determination to support the new central leadership
with Jiang Zemin at the core.
</P>
<P>
A decision passed during the session called on members of
party organizations at all levels to study the documents of the 15
CPC National Congress, and to follow the main theme of the
congress as the guideline for future work of the Zhi Gong Party.
</P>
