<HEADLINE> Sino-ROK Economic Symposium In Changsha </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, October 8 (Xinhua) -- The '97 International Economic
Symposium between China and the Republic of Korea (ROK) opened
today in Zhangjiajie City, central China's Hunan Province.
</P>
<P>
The symposium focused on the role of the high-technology
industry in economic development.
</P>
<P>
Over the next three days, some 70 representatives from China
and ROK will discuss economic development in both countries,
China's economic reform, and Sino-ROK telecommunications
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening ceremony, Duk Woo Nam, director of the
ROK Pacific Institute, noted that it is both urgent and important
for China and the ROK to develop their hi-tech industries. He also
said the two nations can supplement each other and move ahead
together.
</P>
<P>
The 1996 Sino-ROK trade volume surpassed 20 billion US dollars,
three times the 1990 figure, and the ROK is currently China's
third largest trade partner.
</P>
<P>
Experts said the fact that the symposium is held in Changsha
shows that foreign businessmen are paying increasing attention to
development of central and western China. 
</P>
