<HEADLINE> Educators Learn From CPC Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Education circles in the Chinese
capital today held a seminar to study and discuss documents from
the 15th National Congress of the Communist Party of China.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Li Lanqing pointed out that educators should hold
high the great banner of the Deng Xiaoping Theory and uphold the
leadership of the CPC Central Committee with Jiang Zemin at the
core in order to turn a new page on China's education reform.
</P>
<P>
Li, also member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China,
said that understandable materials should be compiled to educate
school students about the guidelines of the CPC National Congress.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that priority should be placed on high quality nine
year compulsory education, and that greater emphasis should be
placed on vocational and adult education.
</P>
<P>
Departments in charge of education should adopt efficient
measures to force various primary and secondary schools to
eliminate the practice of overcharging students, said Li.
</P>
<P>
Li said the Chinese citizens can expect a bright future for
education if teachers win greater respects and funding for
education is increased sharply. 
