reform and scientific research, and have won numerous awards from
ministries and local provinces. Fifteen percent of the teachers
receive government grants as outstanding experts recognized by the
State Council.
</P>
<P>
China's three million undergraduates are required to complete
between four and seven Marxist and ethics courses, with 160,000
postgraduates taking 1-2 courses of political theory. Some 1.5
million adult school students should also complete ethics
courses. 
