<HEADLINE> India's Power Output Up in First Half Fiscal Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 8 (Xinhua) -- The overall power generation
in India during the first six months of this fiscal year (April 1,
1997-March 31, 1998) grew by 7 percent over a year earlier,
official sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
A total of 204.74 billion units of electricity was generated
during the first half of the current financial year as against
191.37 billion units last year.
</P>
<P>
Efforts have been made to increase the plant load factor of the
thermal power plants, which account for almost three-fourths of
electricity generation in the country, from 64.3 percent last year
to 65.4 percent this year.
</P>
<P>
The Indian Power Ministry has been coordinating with the state
governments and other utilities to ensure that the targeted power
generation growth of 7.2 percent for the current year is
fulfilled, the sources said.  
</P>
