<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Veld fires continue to rage in
South Africa's Northern Province while fires in Eastern Cape were
brought under control, reports said today.
</P>
<P>
Fires in the Northern Province in and around Vaalwater, a city more than
200 kilometers north of Johannesburg, spread to nearby Ellisras area
overnight on Tuesday, South African Press Association said.
</P>
<P>
The flames have destroyed more than 100,000 hactares of grazing land
and between 25 and 40 game and cattle farms. Property worth millions
of Rand has also been damaged.
</P>
<P>
Animals and livestock, including elephants and rhino, were endangered.
</P>
<P>
South African Air Force spokeswoman Laverne Machine said today that
a game ranch worth 3 million Rand (640,000 U.S. dollars) was about to
go up in flames.
</P>
<P>
Farmers had to cut down fences around game farms to allow animals
to flee the flames.
</P>
<P>
The Air Force, the army, police, and emergency services, together
with farmers and their workers, joined hands to fight the flames.
</P>
<P>
The fires were suspected to have been started by heat or lightning.
</P>
<P>
Veld fires in Eastern Cape, burning unabated since last Thursday,
was finally contained. Only one fire still burned Tuesday night.
</P>
