<HEADLINE> China's First Coast Defence Museum Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, October 8 (Xinhua) -- China's first coast defence
museum opened today in Ningbo, Zhejiang Province in east China.
</P>
<P>
The museum is located in Zhenghai, an important military port
since ancient time and also a great battle field where the Chinese
people fought against foreign invasions by Japan, Britain and
France in modern history.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, during its construction, the museum
recieved some 109 million yuan donated by over 200 organizations
and about 52,000 individuals, including lots of overseas Chinese.
</P>
<P>
Central and local authorities have made the museum a base for
education in patriotism. 
</P>
</TEXT>
