<HEADLINE> Jiang Congratulates Kim's Election as DPRK Party Chief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Jiang Zemin, general secretary
of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China, today
congratulated Comrade Kim Jong Il, leader of the Democratic
People's Republic of Korea (DPRK), on his assumption of office as
general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea (WPK).
</P>
<P>
In his congratulatory message, Jiang said, "since Comrade Kim
Il Sung passed away three year ago, the people of the DPRK have
rallied closely around the WPK Central Committee under your
leadership and carried out Comrade Kim Il Sung's behests."
</P>
<P>
With iron will and strong determination, the people of the DPRK
have overcome all kinds of difficulties and hardships through
their own efforts, he said.
</P>
<P>
The people of the DPRK will continue to march on along the road
of building their motherland, striving for the peaceful
unification of the country and safeguarding peace and stability on
the Korean Peninsula, he added.
</P>
<P>
China and the DPRK are friendly neighbors linked by common
mountains and rivers, he said. "There exists a time-tested
traditional friendship between the two parties, two countries and
two peoples, which was personally fostered and developed by the
leaders of older generation of our two countries."
</P>
<P>
Consolidating and developing the Sino-DPRK friendly and
cooperative ties is not only in the fundermental interests of the
two parties, two countries and two peoples, but also of great
significance for promoting peace, stability and development on the
Korean Peninsula, in Northeast Asia and even the whole world, he
noted.
</P>
<P>
"We will, as always, make unremitting efforts to further
strengthen and develop the Sino-DPRK friendly and cooperative
relations," he said.
</P>
<P>
"We believe that with our joint efforts, the Sino-DPRK
traditional friendship and good-neighborly ties will surely be
developed and passed on from generation to generation," he added.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also wished Kim Jong Il and the WPK greater success in
their future work. 
</P>
</TEXT>
