<HEADLINE> Ding Guangen On Publicizing Guidelines of Party Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Ding Guangen, head of the
Propaganda Department of Central Committee of the Communist Party
of China (CPC), urged propaganda officials at all levels to make
great efforts to publicizing the guidelines of the Party's 15th
national congress and mobilize the people of the whole country to
strive for the realization of the objectives set forth by the
Party's congress.
</P>
<P>
Ding, who is a member of the Politburo and a member of the
Secretariat, of the CPC Central Committee, made the call during a
recent inspection tour in east China's Anhui Province where he
exchanged views with local propaganda officials on how to carry
out the guidelines of the 15th National Party Congress.
</P>
<P>
Officials in propaganda departments must first of all study and
grasp the gist of the Party congress if they are to do a good
publicizing work, said Ding who also serves as head of the Central
Commission for Guiding the Cultural and Ethical Progress.
</P>
<P>
While getting across the main ideas of the report by Jiang
Zemin at the congress, propaganda officials should conduct more
investigations so that their lectures are more convincing.
</P>
<P>
"We should guard against empty talk, avoid taking one-sided
approach in understanding the guidelines and falling into
absoluteness," Ding said.
</P>
<P>
Ding gave credits to the achievement Anhui has made in building
model cities, pointing out that promoting ethical and cultural
progress is a long-term task and should be carried out under the
guidelines of the Party congress.
</P>
<P>
"The key to promoting the ethical and cultural progress is
that we should serve the people and solve their practical problems
and concern ourselves with issues that touch their lives," said
the top Party propaganda official.  
</P>
</TEXT>
