<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 8 (Xinhua) -- At least 10 people were injured
this evening when a commuter train collided with a packed
passenger bus in the capital city, police said.
</P>
<P>
Police said all the injured, some of them in serious condition,
have been rushed to nearby hospitals.
</P>
<P>
The collision took place when the bus was crossing the
intersection of the railway and Buendia Avenue in Makati City,
Metro Manila.
</P>
<P>
The train smashed into the bus and pulled it a few meters away
before being stopped, a witness said.
</P>
<P>
Late last month, a commuter train collided with two cars
detached from another train in a southern Manila suburb, leaving
nine dead and more than 300 others injured.  
