<HEADLINE> Chinese, Italian Defense Ministers Hold Talks in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Defense Minister Chi
Haotian held talks this evening with Italian Defense Minister
Beniamino Andreatta.
</P>
<P>
Chi, vice-chairman of the Central Military Commission and state
councillor, noted that the Chinese government always values
developing friendship and cooperation with Italy, an important
country in Western Europe.
</P>
<P>
High-level exchanges between the two countries in recent years
have turned a new page in Sino-Italian relations, said Chi.
</P>
<P>
He also pointed to the rapid development of relations between
the two armed forces, an important component in Sino-Italian
ties. He noted that said development can be seen in increasing
exchanges of visits between leaders of the two armed forces and in
active cooperation in the technical field.
</P>
<P>
Exchanges, which have helped to enhance mutual understanding
and provided an opportunity to learn from each other, have been
conducive to the building of the armed forces of both nations,
said Chi.
</P>
<P>
He said that Andreatta's visit not only will promote exchanges
between the two defense departments and enhance relations between
the two armed forces, but will also contribute to the overall
development of friendly bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Andreatta said that he and his colleagues are visiting at an
important time following the recent 15th National Congress of the
Chinese Communist Party which attracted worldwide attention.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the number of visits by military
delegations from many countries clearly illustrates China's
increasing role in Asia and the world as a whole.
</P>
<P>
Andreatta said that continued growth in bilateral relations
will enable the two armed forces to exchange views during frequent
reciprocal visits.
</P>
<P>
The leaders also exchanged views on the international situation
and other issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
Chi presided over an earlier welcoming ceremony for Andreatta
who arrived today as a guest of the Chinese Defense Minister.
</P>
