<HEADLINE> Macao, Guangdong Police Launch Joint Exercise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Police departments in Macao
and south China's Guangdong Province today launched a joint
land-sea exercise to strengthen efforts to combat illegal
immigration between Macao and Zhuhai.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong public security departments dispatched some 2,000
policemen, 53 ships and 60 vehicles for the exercise which is
designed to stop illegal immigrants from leaving the mainland and
entering Macao.
</P>
<P>
Macao police agencies provided seven ships for coordination,
and increased patrols in border areas.
</P>
<P>
"The goal of the exercise was to enhance cooperation between
the two sides in the battle against illegal activities and ensure
Macao's smooth return to the motherland in 1999," according to
Chen Shaoji, an official with the Guangdong Public Security Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Public security departments in Zhuhai have handled 61 illegal
immigration cases since last year, and have seized 498 illegal
immigrants. 
