<HEADLINE> Cholera Kills 118 in South-Western Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, October 8 (Xinhua) -- A cholera outbreak in Nyanza
Province, south-western Kenya, so far has killed 118 people in
four months, the Daily Nation newspaper reported today.
</P>
<P>
Ten people died of the disease in Migori and Rachuonyo
districts between last Friday and Sunday night, a medical source
was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Some areas where cholera is biting in are short of drugs and
only get a limited supply of oral rehydration fluids, thus
worsening the situation, said the report.
</P>
<P>
It seems more deaths go unreported as they occur deep in the
rural areas, said the report.
</P>
<P>
However, the government has dispatched medical teams to tour
the affected areas, in a bid to curb cholera's spreading, which
is fueled by lack of clean drinking water and poor sanitation.
</P>
</TEXT>
