<HEADLINE> Ethiopia to Have First Private University </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Initial step has been taken
toward establishing the first private university in Ethiopia
sometime next year, the government newspaper, The Ethiopian
Herald, reported today.
</P>
<P>
Quoting a U.S. information service press release, the report
said, the proposed institution is reportedly intended to provide
"American-style education" to students from surrounding countries
as well.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, investors and U.S. university
represen- tatives reached the decision to "develop" the American
University of Ethiopia (AUE) last Sunday and later visited the
future site north of the capital.
</P>
<P>
The occasion marked the signing of an agreement providing for
the creation of the university between founding investors and
California State University (CSU), Stanislaus.
</P>
<P>
The report said the initiative was taken in response to
sustained interest by faculty who have taken sabbatical or
used vacation time to serve the sub-region.
</P>
<P>
The AUE founding investors were quoted by the report as saying
that the purpose is not only to provide "badly needed additional
places for qualified university students" but also create "a
dynamic resource for technological transfer and human resource
development". 
</P>
