<HEADLINE> China Stresses Anti-Corruption: Premier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng said
here today that China attaches great importance to
anti-corruption, which is an extremely important part of the Party
and government work.
</P>
<P>
"This is an important guarantee for the success of the
country's cause of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics," the premier stressed.
</P>
<P>
Li made the remarks at a meeting with a delegation from the
Republic of Korea (ROK) led by Shi-Yoon Lee, chairman of the Board
of Audit and Inspection of the ROK, in Zhongnanhai, site of the
Central Government.
</P>
<P>
After briefing the ROK guests on China's work of supervision,
Li Peng said the Chinese Communist Party and the Central
Government have always attached great importance to discipline
inspection and the supervisory work of the government
functionaries and public servants, advocating diligent work and a
clean government.
</P>
<P>
"We are intensifying our efforts in this regard so as to ensure
that the Party discipline and the state laws and regulations are
strictly observed," Li said, adding that relevant departments are
stepping up their work to improve education, legislation and
supervision in this field.
</P>
<P>
China's supervision departments and the ROK Board of Audit and
Inspection have established good working relations and have had
many beneficial exchanges, Li noted, hoping that there will be
more such exchanges between the two sides in the years to come.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Minister of Supervision Cao Qingze was present at the
meeting. 
