<HEADLINE> Yang Lan Wins Women's 1-m Springboard at National Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Yang Lan of Jiangsu Province
won the women's one-meter springboard title with a nearly perfect
last dive at the eighth Chinese National Games here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Yang, World Cup champion in 1995, did not catch up with Yan Jie
of Chinese Army until the last dive, which earned her the day's
highest score of 73.47 points and the gold medal.
</P>
<P>
Yan, who scored only 56.16 points in the final dive,
accumulated 291.66 points to take the second place, 11.82 behind
Yang. The third place went to Zhang Jing, also representing
Chinese Army.
</P>
<P>
"I was confident when I stood on the board for the decisive
last dive," Yang said, " I did not think of winning the gold.
What came across my mind was to make a brilliant dive."
</P>
<P>
Yang's coach Jin Haiquan was also satisfied with his protegee's
performance.
</P>
<P>
"This was the highest-level competition of the one-meter
springboard event over the past few years, nationally or
internationally," Jin said, "She was consistent both physically
and mentally." 
</P>
</TEXT>
