<DOCNO> XIE19971008.0145 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Manila Releases More Fund to Fight Against El Nino </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 8 (Xinhua) -- President Fidel Ramos said today
that he has ordered the release of an extra 700 million pesos
(19.7 million U.S. dollars) for water projects as part of the
government's effort to mitigate the effects of the El Nino
phenomenon.
</P>
<P>
At his weekly press conference, Ramos said the fund was in
addition to the 800 million pesos (22.5 million dollars) released
in the past two weeks for water projects.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the release of the funds is really intended to
create people's awareness about the need to save water now, even
if it is still raining these days.
</P>
<P>
The new fund will be used for small water impounding projects
and small farm reservoirs for communities, water conservation and
water recycling in order to ease possible drought caused by El
Nino.
</P>
<P>
El Nino, a large-scale meteorological phenomenon that develops
in the Pacific Ocean, is associated with extreme climatic
variability such as devastating drought, winds and rains.
</P>
<P>
Weathermen forecast that El Nino will strike the country and
its Southeast Asian neighbors late this year and is expected to
last for eight months.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
