<HEADLINE> Manila to Host Meeting on Asian Marine Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 8 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines is planning to
convene an international workshop on Asian maritime environment
protection this year under the auspices of the ASEAN-Europe
Meeting (ASEM), the Philippine News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The ASEM is a forum between the Association of Southeast Asian
Nations and the European Union and tackles various areas of
cooperation between them ranging from economic issues to
environmental concerns.
</P>
<P>
The planned meeting will be called the Working Group Conference
on Maritime Environment Protection Cooperation in the Seas of
Asia, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
The conference is an initiative raised by the Philippines
during the first ASEM leaders summit held in Bangkok last year.
</P>
<P>
The agency quoted Philippine Foreign Secretary Domingo Siazon
as saying the workshop will be attended by marine environment
experts from academic and research institutions in ASEM
participating countries.
</P>
<P>
Siazon said the Philippine initiative on the marine environment
is deemed important due to the urgency of environmental
conservation and the protection of marine life in the ASEAN
region.  
</P>
</TEXT>
