<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Drug Research Symposium Opens in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 8 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese health official today
said that China must improve the level of its drug research and
strengthen regulation of new drug development in order to gain a
greater share of the international drug market.
</P>
<P>
Shao Mingli, director of the Drug Policy and Administration
Bureau under the Ministry of Health (MOH), noted that China
still lags far behind developed countries in terms of
undertaking and analyzing drug-related clinical research.
</P>
<P>
Shao made the remarks during an international symposium on the
clinical development of drugs and the application of statistics,
which opened here today.
</P>
<P>
Clinical research is one of the most important components in
the drug development process, with experts noting that global drug
development and international cooperation are emerging as a major
trend in pharmaceutical research, development and regulation.
</P>
<P>
"China, a large emerging market for pharmaceutical products, is
becoming an increasingly important player in collaborative
clinical research and drug development," said Ling Su
from US-based Merck Research Laboratories.
</P>
<P>
The event marks the first time China has invited hundreds of
overseas drug policy-makers and clinical researchers to discuss
clinical research and product regulation with Chinese counterparts.
</P>
<P>
Participants came from a number of countries and regions,
including the United States, Britain, and Singapore.
</P>
<P>
The two-day event was jointly sponsored by the Drug Policy and
Administration Bureau, the MOH Center for Drug Evaluation, and
the Drug Information Association of the United States. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
