<DOCNO> XIE19971008.0153 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Stock Market Reports Slim Trading </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 8 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai stock market
reported sliding prices and shrinking trade in September.
</P>
<P>
Statistics released by the Shanghai Securities Exchange show
that the Composite Stock Index closed at 1,097.38 last month, down
10.13 percent from the previous month, with the blue chip SSE-30
index dropping by 9.97 percent to 3,392.20.
</P>
<P>
The stock trading volume ended at 78.30 billion yuan, down 6.93
percent from the August figure.
</P>
<P>
Local stock analysts note that the overall market performance
for September was less than optimistic, but that stock prices for
enterprises slated for mergers or acquisition attracted great
attention from investors.
</P>
<P>
The trading volume for B shares available to foreign investors
plunged nearly 50 percent to 1.61 billion yuan, with the B Share
Index falling 8.67 percent to 76.31.
</P>
<P>
However, the local treasury bond market witnessed brisk trading
during the period, climbing by 20 percent to 85.63 billion yuan by
the end of the month.
</P>
<P>
The funds market gradually recovered from a downward trend
amidst spreading market news that the government may soon unveil a
set of regulations concerning investment funds. The total trading
volume for the month stood at 1.563 billion yuan, up 260 million
yuan from August. 
</P>
</TEXT>
