<HEADLINE> Scholars Highlight Role of Science and Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 8 (Xinhua) -- A symposium on the relationship
between Deng Xiaoping Theory and the development of modern science
and technology was held today in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The symposium, jointly sponsored by the Chinese Association of
Science and Technology and People's Daily, featured discussions on
the guidance Deng Xiaoping Theory has provided to the reform,
opening and modernization drives.
</P>
<P>
Gong Yuzhi, vice-president of the Party School of the Communist
Party of China (CPC) Central Committee, noted that Deng clearly
defined the critical role of science and technology in socialist
modernization construction.
</P>
<P>
"His clarification that 'science and technology is the primary
productive force' is characterized by the distinctive flavor of
the day," said Gong.
</P>
<P>
More than 40 experts and scholars attending the symposium
agreed that China should give full play to science and technology
to develop productive forces. They pledged to increase research
efforts and offer more advice for promoting the nation's further
growth.
</P>
<P>
Experts and scholars also tabled many helpful proposals on the
development of science and technology, including the need for
increased funding.  
</P>
</TEXT>
