<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Meets Foreign Ambassadors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng met here
today with outgoing and new ambassadors to China from six
countries.
</P>
<P>
During his meeting with Sven Linder and Dang Nghiem Hoanh,
outgoing ambassadors of Sweden and Vietnam respectively, Li
expressed his appreciations for the efforts of the two ambassadors
to promote the development of the bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Li expressed his hope that the four new ambassadors would tour
various areas of China to increase their understanding of his
country. Chinese government would provide necessary help and
convenience for their work, he added.
</P>
<P>
The four new ambassadors are Mohammed Hamad Al-Mahmeed from
Bahrain, Barney Rongap from Papua New Guinea, Pasi Rutanen from
Finland, and E.Ameyedowo from Ghana. 
</P>
