<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Garment, Textile Exports Increase in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Garment and textile exports in
the Philippines during the first nine months of the year reached
2.25 billion U.S. dollars, up by 7.8 percent from last year's 2.09
billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Data released by the Garments and Textile Export Board today
showed that the United States remained the biggest market with
purchases amounting to 1.75 billion dollars from 1.6 billion
dollars in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Receipts from Canada also improved by 12.5 percent from 41
million dollars to 46 million dollars while those from Europe
slightly declined by 1.77 percent from 307 million dollars to
301.6 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Purchases of apparel reached 1.8 billion dollars from 1.7
billion dollars while those of non-apparel and textiles amounted
to 268.4 million dollars and 168.4 million dollars from 232.5
million dollars and 141.6 million dollars respectively.  
</P>
</TEXT>
