<HEADLINE> Longo Wins Time Trial Title in Cycling Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Jeannie Longo won the women's
time trial title at the world road cycling championships in San
Sebastian, Spain, on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The 39-year-old French ride sprinted home at 39 minutes 15
seconds over a 28 kilometers circuit to snatch her eighth world
road title. Her first title had come 12 years ago.
</P>
<P>
Russian Zoulfia Zabirova, who beat Longo to take the Olympic
time trial crown in Atlanta last year, clocked 0.85 seconds slower
for second place.
</P>
<P>
The bronze medal went to Germany's Judith Arndt, who was 29
seconds outside Longo's time. 
</P>
