<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Meets Indonesian Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng
expressed his satisfaction with the smooth development of
Sino-Indonesian ties today during his meeting with Indonesian
Minister of Defense and Security Edi Sudrajat.
</P>
<P>
Li said the two countries have maintained high-level exchanges
since the resumption of diplomatic ties in 1990, and have
constantly promoted cooperation in international affairs by
sharing views on many major international and regional issues.
</P>
<P>
China is pleased that the armied forces of the two countries
have furthered their relations, said Li, adding that ties between
the two countries and their armied forces should be enhanced.
</P>
<P>
He noted that China takes economic construction as its central
task and pursues a diplomatic policy of independence.
</P>
<P>
Seeking good-neighborly ties with surrounding countries
constitutes an important part of China's foreign policy, said Li,
adding that establishing cooperative ties with Southest Asian
nations is China's long-term goal.
</P>
<P>
Edi conveyed Indonesian President Soeharto's best regards to
Chinese President Jiang Zemin and Premier Li Peng. Edi said that
Soeharto highly values the important policy decisions made during
the recent 15th National Congress of the Chinese Communist
Party. He said the decisions are not only significant to China,
but also to the Asia-Pacific region and the world as a whole.
</P>
<P>
Soeharto voiced satisfaction with the current Sino-Indonesian
ties, saying that the current favorable development trend will be
maintained.
</P>
<P>
Edi added that Indonesia appreciates China's important
contributions to the peace and stability in the region.
</P>
<P>
Li asked Edi to convey his and President Jiang's best regards
to Soeharto.
</P>
<P>
Li expressed the Chinese government's concern for losses
resulting from the forest fire in Indonesia. He said that under
the leadership of President Soeharto and the Indonesian
government, the Indonesian people will surely conquer the
disaster. 
</P>
</TEXT>
