<HEADLINE> 4.3 Millions Dollars at Stake in Beach Volleyball </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, October 8 (Xinhua) -- A record 4.3 million U.S. dollars
in prize money will be on offer during the 1998 Beach Volleyball
World Tour, the International Volleyball Federation said in
Lausanne on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The tour consists of 16 men's and 11 women's tournaments,
including the Goodwill Games in New York in July, said the world
volleyball ruling body.
</P>
<P>
The total 1998 prize money for men will be 2.6 million dollars,
with 1.72 million dollars for the women. 
