<HEADLINE> Share Prices Rally on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Share prices rallied on the
Singapore market today as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials
Index rose steadily throughout the day and closed at 1882.03
points, 1.69 points higher than Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Total market volume surged to 303.91 million units, valued at
442.74 million Singapore dollars (about 287.49 million U.S.
dollars). Advances overwhelmed declines by 259 to 83, while 275
other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Local computer maker IPC Corporation was the most actively
traded stock as it registered a turnover of 49.17 million units.
It was followed by RHB Capital Warrant99 which had 18.49 million
units traded. Rekapac was next with 18.08 million shares changed
hands.
</P>
<P>
The Development Bank of Singapore (DBS) Foreign led the gainers
of the day as it rose 90 cents to finish at 15.3 Singapore
dollars. Creative 50 gained 80 cents to end at 39.8 Singapore
dollars, while Malaya Banking and Malaya Banking 200 increased 60
cents each to close at 8.4 and 8.3 dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, UMW Warrant was the biggest loser as it
declined 3.27 dollars to end at 1.07 dollars. The Singapore Press
Holdings (SPH) Foreign fell 1.6 dollars to close at 21.2 Singapore
dollars. Datacraft was 23 cents lower at 2.36 U.S. dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
