<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rule of Law to Be Maintained in Hong Kong: Tung </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Chief Executive of the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) Tung Chee Hwa said he is
confident that the Judiciary will continue to uphold the rule of
law in Hong Kong by dispensing justice without fear or favor.
</P>
<P>
Delivering his first Policy Address this afternoon, Tung said a
credible and independent judicial system underpins Hong Kong's
present success. The Basic Law provides for the continuation of
the rule of law and the judicial system beyond July 1 with no
fundamental changes, and the judicial system continues to operate
fairly and independently as before.
</P>
<P>
He said that with the establishment of the Court of Final
Appeal of the HKSAR, for the first time in history Hong Kong has a
fully integrated system of courts. Another milestone in the
judicial system has been the establishment of a bilingual court
system in which the Chinese language can be used along with the
English language.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that further improvements will be made to the legal
aid system.
</P>
<P>
He also pledged that the government is determined to maintain
the police force as one of the finest in the world and further
improve its effectiveness.
</P>
<P>
"Let me make it clear that the SAR will not tolerate any form
of corruption," he stressed. "The SAR government is committed to
the fight against corruption in every area of public and private
life."
</P>
<P>
Talking about the system of government, Tung said his
administration is devoting attention to preparing for the election
of the first SAR Legislature and to the steady development of Hong
Kong's democracy.
</P>
<P>
"We have just established the Electoral Affairs Commission to
oversee the elections, to ensure that they are carried out openly
and fairly," he said, adding that a vigorous, territory-wide
campaign to register voters and update the electoral roll will be
conducted.
</P>
<P>
He said Hong Kong has a dedicated, honest and efficient civil
service that has gained the deep respect of the local and
international community alike.
</P>
<P>
"I've tasked the Secretary for the Treasury to lead a special
group to develop and implement a target-based management process
to achieve continuous improvement in public services," he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
