<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks End Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Interest rate-sensitive stocks
underpinned a firmer close on the Australian share market amid
cautious optimism that the Reserve Bank of Australia (RBA) could
cut rates in the coming weeks.
</P>
<P>
The all ordinaries index ended at its high for the day, up 14.1
points at 2768.4.
</P>
<P>
Brokers said investors were moving into the "more secure end of
the market" because of a general lack of direction domestically.
Economists also believe there is still an opportunity for the RBA
to cut rates.
</P>
<P>
The RBA today maintained its silence on rates following its
October board meeting Tuesday to consider monetary policy.
</P>
<P>
The all industrials index lifted 27.9 points to 4556.5, while
the all resources index added 2.7 points to 1361.0.
</P>
<P>
The banking index put on 47.4 points to 5541.5, with Westpac
Bank gaining 23.2 cents to 8.83 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
Commonwealth Bank rose 14.5 cents, ANZ added three cents and
NAB rose 9.6 cents.
</P>
<P>
On the resources side, BHP and Rio Tinto ended flat at 16.07
and 21.05 Australian dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
The gold index eased 1.1 to 1334.9 points, with gold bullion
closing at 331.75 dollars an ounce from 331.85 previously.
</P>
<P>
National turnover totaled 331.57 million shares traded valued
at 737.31 million Australian dollars (534.54 million U.S.
dollars), with falling issues outnumbering rises 548 to 526.
</P>
</TEXT>
