<DOCNO> XIE19971008.0212 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Navy Intercepts Fuel Boat for Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, October 8 (Xinhua) -- An Indian boat carrying a large
stock of fuel for the Tamil rebels was intercepted by the Sri
Lankan Navy in the north Tuesday, according to reports monitored
here today.
</P>
<P>
A Sri Lankan naval boat intercepted the Indian boat and
arrested four Indian Tamils.
</P>
<P>
There were more than 1,000 liters of lubricant, 1,200 liters of
petrol and 125 liters of battery acid on the boat. A new portable
generator was also found with the stock, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
The suspects confessed to the Sri Lankan military that they
were transporting the fuel for the Liberation Tigers of Tamil
Eelam (LTTE) in Irananitivu in the north.
</P>
<P>
Investigations are still underway.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been fighting a bloody ethnic war for a separate
state of their own in the north and east of the island country for
14 years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
