<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Highest Cave Group Discovered In Chongqing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, October 8 (Xinhua) -- A newly-discovered limestone
cave at the top of Jingfo Mountain (Golden Buddha Mountain) in
Chongqing, the new municipality in southwest China, is the highest
in China, a cave researcher says.
</P>
<P>
It is also one of the oldest geologically, says professor Zhu
Xuewen, president of the China Cave Research Society. It is more
than 10 km in length, and contains ruins of an ancient mine.
</P>
<P>
Golden Buddha Mountain is 2,251 meters above sea level, and has
more than 5,000 species of plants. Just below the top of the
mountain is a large series of caves, most of them large, with the
biggest being 130 meters wide with a ceiling nearly 50 meters high.
</P>
<P>
These caves are connected by underground passages. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
