<HEADLINE> Traditional Chinese Therapy Being Used In Argentina </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, October 8 (Xinhua) -- A rehabilitation center opened
recently in Buenos Aires, the capital of Argentina, bringing
traditional Chinese medical practices to South America.
</P>
<P>
One couple who were above 60, suffered from lumbar vertebrae
problems for more than 20 years, but after visiting the center,
they found the therapy effective.
</P>
<P>
The center is run by five doctors from the Tanggangzi
Physiotherapy Hospital, in the city of Anshan, Liaoning Province,
in northwest China.
</P>
<P>
The hospital has hot springs and Asia's only hot mud. The
doctors use more than 70 physiotherapy and traditional Chinese
therapeutic methods like massage and acupuncture to treat
rheumatism, lumbar vertebrae problems, skin diseases, and other
chronic ailments.
</P>
<P>
It has treated more than 300 Argentine patients and has been
well received by local people.  
</P>
</TEXT>
