<HEADLINE> Large-Scale Basic Construction in Central China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Henan province
has plans to put more than 300 billion yuan into 284 large and
medium-sized construction projects during the 1996-2000 period.
</P>
<P>
More than half of the projects are new ones mostly in hi-tech
and infrastructure constructions and local leading industries.
</P>
<P>
The work is expected to improve the economy and investment
environment in the province, which has the largest population in
the nation.
</P>
<P>
It has been encouraged by policies to speed up economic
development in central and western parts of the country, and these
areas want to become attractive spots for overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
Since 1996, the province has built 11 large projects, including
ethylene and power plants, reservoirs, and a highway linking the
capital city of Zhengzhou with Kaifeng, one of the country's
ancient capitals. 
</P>
