<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0800 GMT, October 8 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG -- Chief Executive of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR) Tung Chee Hwa began delivering his
first policy address before the Provisional Legislative Council
here Wednesday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Tung, who gave the address, delivered precisely 100 days after
the establishment of the HKSAR on July 1, told reporters Tuesday
that he had taken into account the interests of all circles of
Hong Kong people while drawing up the address.
(Hong Kong-Tung-Policy Address)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BELGRADE -- Yugoslav President Slobodan Milosevic Tuesday
stressed that the Organization for Security and Cooperation in
Europe (OSCE) monitoring the Serb parliamentary and presidential
elections in Bosnia should take an objective and impartial stand.
</P>
<P>
Milosevic made the remark during a meeting with Robert Frovik,
OSCE representative in Bosnia, to discuss the peace process in
war-torn Bosnia. (Yugoslavia-OSCE)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russian Foreign Ministry spokesman Gennady Tarasov
said Tuesday that Russia will not give up its role in Balkan
affairs.
</P>
<P>
While being asked by a reporter at a news conference why Russia
had not been invited to attend the meeting of defense ministers of
southeast European countries last Friday in Bulgaria's capital
Sofia, Tarasov said it was inappropriate for the organizer to make
the conference have the nature of a "bloc" and to restrict
participants according to their proximity to the NATO and its
membership. (Russia-Balkans)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BUDAPEST -- The Hungarian National Assembly decided Tuesday to
hold a referendum on November 16 on the country's entry into the
North Atlantic Treaty Organization.
</P>
<P>
The referendum move was adopted by a two-third majority.
Opposition members of parliament withdrew from voting as a sign of
protest.
</P>
<P>
NATO decided in early July to admit Hungary, Poland and the
Czech Republic into the organization. Poland and the Czech
Republic will not conduct any referendum on the issue.
(Hungary-NATO-Referendum)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- The Secretary-General of the Organization for
Economic Cooperation and Development (OECD) Donald Johnston said
here Tuesday that the OECD has agreed in principle to admit Russia
but has not decided on when to grant the country membership.
</P>
<P>
However, he said, Russia still has much to do and has to
complete all required reforms to standardize its economy before
its entry into the economic organization. (OECD-Russia)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Palestinian President Yasser Arafat and Israeli Prime
Minister Benjamin Netanyahu met Wednesday for their first talks in
eight months on the stalled Middle East peace progress.
</P>
<P>
According to media reports reaching here, the two leaders met
at the Erez checkpoint on the border between Israel and the Gaza
Strip. The meeting between the two leaders was the first since
peace talks were suspended in March after Israel launched a Jewish
settlement in Arab East Jerusalem. (Arafat-Netanyahu-Meeting)
</P>
</TEXT>
