<HEADLINE> International Sister-City Trade Fair Opens in Northeast China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, October 8 (Xinhua) -- A five-day international
sister-city trade fair opened today in the coastal city of Dalian
in northeast China's Liaoning province.
</P>
<P>
It is the largest fair of its kind ever held in Dalian and
attracts more than 220 enterprises from 14 countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
Some big-name companies like Japan's Matsushita and Sanyo and
some representative groups from Switzerland, Malaysia, and Turkey
are attending the fair.
</P>
<P>
More than 10 categories of items are on display, ranging from
machinery, textiles, petrochemicals, environmental protection,
medical and health care products, sanitation equipment, and
building materials to arts and crafts. 
</P>
