<HEADLINE> Albania Signs Memorandum With IMF </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Albanian Prime Minister Fatos
Nano signed a memorandum with the International Monetary Fund
today, paving the way for the organization to aid Albania in the
next six months.
</P>
<P>
The memorandum will serve as an "agreement of guarantee" under
which the IMF will provide "post-conflict emergency aid" to Albania.
</P>
<P>
Albania pledged in the memorandum to raise the value-added tax
from 12.5 percent to 20 percent, adopt intense economic reform and
prohibit economic activities of the firms that illegally collect
funds with high interest.
</P>
<P>
Nano said after the signing that this document will provide
a guarantee for investment flow into his country.
</P>
<P>
According to the agreement between Albania and the IMF, the
organization will sign an agreement on aid to Albania for three
years if Tirana can abide by its promise in the next six months.
</P>
</TEXT>
