<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Approves 9 Projects Involving 451 Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, October 8 (Xinhua) -- The Executive Committee of the
National Economic Committee (ECNEC) of Bangladesh has approved
nine projects involving 20.05 billion taka (about 451.17 million
U.S. dollars), a local newspaper reported today.
</P>
<P>
Of the total projects, 3.3 billion taka (about 74.25 million
dollars) would be spent for developing communication system in the
rural areas through construction of bridges and culverts to boost
up agriculture and commerce in the areas, the Bangladesh Times
said.
</P>
<P>
Under the project, 1,230 km of "B" category roads and 340 km
rural roads will be developed while 2000 meters of "B" type
culverts and 6,730 km bridges and culverts on rural roads will be
built, the newspaper noted.
</P>
<P>
Under the second project, 1.797 billion taka (about 40.32
million dollars) will be spent to strengthen rural economy by
creating opportunities for sustainable activities focusing on the
identified rural growth centers, the newspaper continued.
</P>
<P>
Under the project, 356 growth centers would be connected with
national highway bridges, the newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
The other projects, the newspaper added, include a series of
construction items in social, educational and medical fields.
</P>
</TEXT>
