<HEADLINE> Technology Boosts Northeast China City's Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Technology upgrading efforts in
some 1,600 industrial businesses of northeast China's port city of
Dalian have resulted in great improvement of their equipment and
products.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics released at a recent meeting on
Dalian's technology upgrading program organized by the city
government, 6,868 projects, with a total investment of 20.4
billion yuan, have been completed since early 1980s when the
program started.
</P>
<P>
For every one yuan of investment, a 1.9 yuan-worth output was
produced, with a pre-tax value of 0.35 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Local officials said technology-oriented investment has
increased the industrial strength of Dalian. The fixed assets of
the city's industry are now estimated at more than 60 billion
yuan, rising from early 1980s' four billion yuan. 
</P>
