<HEADLINE> hke100820 - India's Silk Industry to Use New Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 8 (Xinhua) -- India's silk industry would
use a new scheme to promote multi-end reeling technology to make
the production more efficient, a government official said here
today.
</P>
<P>
The scheme would promote use of six basin and 10 basin upgraded
reeling technology package developed by the Central Silk
Technological Research Institute of the Central Silk Board (CSB).
</P>
<P>
The scheme envisages establishment of 300 multi-end reeling
units in the first phase over three years, the official said.
</P>
<P>
The scheme has been offered to all states in the country and
envisages a subsidy of 30 percent, shared equally by the Center
and the respective state governments.
</P>
<P>
Besides supplying quality silk worm seed and mulberry cuttings,
CSB also undertakes directly or jointly with the state sericulture
departments the implementation of various sericulture projects,
the same source said.  
</P>
