<HEADLINE> Thai PM Leaves for Japan Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Thai Prime Minister Chavalit
Yongchaiyudh left for Japan today on a three-day official visit.
</P>
<P>
He is being accompanied by a strong entourage, which includes
Deputy Prime Minister and concurrently Industry Minister Korn
Dabbaransi, Finance Minister Thanong Bidaya, Foreign Minister
Prachuab Chaiyasarn, Commerce Minister Narongchai Akrasanee and a
number of leading business executives.
</P>
<P>
The visit is aimed at boosting bilateral economic and trade
ties and investment.
</P>
<P>
