representatives from key industries to brief them about Thailand's
policy on foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, it was reported that Thailand will ask Japan to extend
the repayment terms for debts incurred by Thai private firms and
seek cooperation to allow Thai companies to buy back controlling
shares which have been acquired by Japanese shareholders, once the
Thai economy recovers.
</P>
<P>
Japan is the largest foreign investor in Thailand and has
played a major role in contributing to the 17.2 billion US dollar
standby credit, arranged by the International Monetary Fund (IMF),
to help Thailand shore up its foreign reserves.  
</P>
