<HEADLINE> Thailand to Get 500 Million Dollar Loan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Five international lending
sources, led by the Industrial Bank of Japan, have agreed to
extend 500 million US dollars to assist Thailand's export-oriented
manufacturers, according to the Export and Import Bank of Thailand
(Exim Bank).
</P>
<P>
The loan agreement is due to be signed next week and the funds
would be available for re-lending to manufacturers through
commercial banks from October 20, Pridiyathorn Devakula, president
of the Exim Bank, was quoted by local press as saying.
</P>
<P>
He said only manufacturers who produce goods for export would
be eligible for the loans.
</P>
<P>
The Exim Bank will re-lend the 500 million dollars to local
commercial banks at one percentage point above the London
interbank offered rate (LIBOR). The banks will then extend loans
to manufacturers at three points above LIBOR.
</P>
<P>
The loan has a one-year repayment period, Pridiyathorn said.
</P>
