<HEADLINE> Panama to Create University of Americas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Panama will create a
specialized University of the Americas near the shores of the
Panama Canal, a Panamanian official said today.
</P>
<P>
Johana Gonzalez, an official of the Panamanian Assembly, said
the bill to create the university was passed by Panama's
parliament and will be ratified by Panamanian President Ernesto
Perez Balladares.
</P>
<P>
This inter-American education project is part of a wide-ranging
plan the current Panamanian administration is undergoing along the
canal, which will be turned over to Panama at the end of 1999 by
the United States in accordance with the Torrijos-Carter treaty.
</P>
<P>
The military bases and houses left by the U.S. Army in the
canal area are being turned into schools, universities, tourist
zones and industrial and commercial centers.
</P>
<P>
Legislator Carlos Smith said the institution will play a major
role in implementing changes in Panama and the hemisphere. The
new university will serve as a model for universities in the
future, which should have largely social prospects.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of the university aims to foster research,
gain and disseminate knowledge, especially in social and education
oriented subjects, said Smith. 
</P>
</TEXT>
