<HEADLINE> Chilean Farmers Object to the Import of U.S Wheat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Chilean farmers have expressed
their objections to the government's decision to give a green
light to the import of U.S. wheat.
</P>
<P>
Chile's National Agriculture Society Chairman Ricardo Ariztia
said the decision has alarmed experts and members of society.
</P>
<P>
Chile's purchases of wheat from the U.S. were suspended in
March 1996 because of the existence in some American States of a
fungus that attacks wheat.
</P>
<P>
Ariztia said by agreeing to import U.S. wheat, Chile may be
putting its own agricultural products in danger.
</P>
<P>
Currently, Chile has a wheat-cultivating area of 400,000
hectares, which provides jobs to 30,000 people. 
</P>
