<HEADLINE> Car Theft Declines In Ukraine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Car theft declined by 18 percent in
Ukraine in the first eight months of this year, Ukraine's Deputy
Minister of the Interior Vladimir Melnykov said today.
</P>
<P>
So far this year, 4,064 cars were stolen in 2,700 registered
cases, Melnykov said, but in 1996, 8,200 cars were stolen and
2,900 cars were robbed.
</P>
<P>
This is the result of strict police inspection, the deputy
minister said. In an effort to catch more car thieves, Ukrainian
police have been authorized to stop any car at any time on any
spot, and drivers are required to carry many forms of
identification, including a driving license, automobile
registration card, authorization certificate and other documents
to prove identity and ownership. 
</P>
</TEXT>
