<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Negative Attitude Towards Divorce in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 8 (Xinhua) -- A survey of 6,000 married
couples in China has found that most of them have stable marriages
and say "no" to divorce.
</P>
<P>
The study was done in the cities of Shanghai and Harbin and in
Guangzhou and Gansu provinces by the Shanghai Social Academy of
Sciences. It found that only 0.7 percent of those questioned say
they "often" want to divorce, and those who say "sometimes"
account for 10 percent, while "never" was a significant 89 percent.
</P>
<P>
Of those who would like to divorce, 41.2 percent said however
that it "costs too much" and that they don't want "the risk".
</P>
<P>
Eleven percent of the people seemed fairly calm about the
possibility that a spouse could ask for divorce, while 13.3
percent answered "maybe" when asked whether they could accept it.
</P>
<P>
The conclusion was that most couples treat marriage seriously.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
