<HEADLINE> Poor Countries Call for Support in Fighting Desertification </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, October 7 (Xinhua) -- The First Conference of Parties to
the United Nations Convention to Combat Desertification (UNCCD)
convened in Rome today. Developing countries immediately called
for material and financial support to prevent desertification.
</P>
<P>
"The Group of 77 and China", said Tanzanian Minister of State
Bakari Mgonde, "called for all the parties to provide equal
treatment in terms of provisioning available resources to
developing country."
</P>
<P>
"Success in combating desertification and drought, particularly
in developing countries, will depend on their ability to acquire
and utilize the appropriate science and technology," he said.
</P>
<P>
J.E. Afful, Ghanaian environment minister, said African
countries need the continuing support of the international
community in implementing the herculean task of combating
desertification.
</P>
<P>
U.S. delegate John Garamendi argued that there is not a lack of
commitment on the part of the United States to assist developing
countries in their effort to combat desertification.
</P>
<P>
"However, our efforts alone are not enough," he said. "What is
needed is more local involvement."  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
