<HEADLINE> Shandong Has More Than 500 Centenarians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, October 8 (Xinhua) -- The ageing trend of China's
Shandong province is being reflected in the number of people above
80, which is increasing at an annual rate of 3.24 percent.
</P>
<P>
The province now has more than 10 million people above the age
of 60 who account for 11.52 percent of the province's total
population, and over 500 of whom are centenarians.
</P>
<P>
According to an official definition in China, a city or region
that has 10 percent of its population above 60 is declared to be a
"ageing society".
</P>
<P>
Shandong ranks sixth in terms of ageing, after Beijing,
Shanghai, Tianjin, Zhejiang, and Jiangsu. Experts predict the
province will experience an ageing peak around the year 2010.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
