<HEADLINE> Ecuador Denies Arms Race With Peru </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Ecuadoran Defense Minister Ramiro
Ricaurte denied his country plans to buy Sukhoi Sur-27 aircraft,
as an attempt to counter Peru's MIG-29 fleet, local press reported
today.
</P>
<P>
Ricaurte said the allegation is by no means true. While
stressing that Ecuador does not want to participate in an arms
race, he said his country "must keep a well-trained, dissuasive
army for external and internal security."
</P>
<P>
Referring to negotiations between Peru and Ecuador over their
territorial dispute, he said that the "inflexible, longstanding
position of Peru on the territorial issue" is "worrisome."
</P>
<P>
"We are hoping there will be flexibility in Peru's position,"
Ricaurte said.
</P>
<P>
Ecuador and Peru have not reached a solution so far on their
border dispute that led to war between the two in early 1995.
</P>
<P>
"We are confident both countries will reach a dignified,
peaceful and just solution, while at the same time we are ready to
defend the dignity of Ecuador," he said. 
</P>
