<HEADLINE> Daily Exports in South China Province Hits 200 Million US Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Foreign trade in south China's
Guangdong province from January to August had a daily volume of
200 million US dollars, International Business Daily reports.
</P>
<P>
The province has had 45.5 billion US dollars worth of exports
for the period, 27.81 percent more than for the same period of
1996. Imports in the province totaled 29 billion US dollars, 16.21
percent more than for the same period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The province has used 8.94 billion US dollars of overseas
investment in the first eight months of this year, with an
increase of 10.18 percent over the corresponding period of last
year.
</P>
<P>
Compared to the 1996 figure, the province's GDP rose 10.02
percent.  
