<HEADLINE> Inter to Play Libya to Raise Funds for Quake Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Inter Milan will play Libya's
national team Saturday in a charity match to raise funds
for Italy's earthquake victims.
</P>
<P>
The match, which organizers said Tuesday will be played in
Varese, is a rare one on foreign soil for Libya.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. Security Council imposed economic, arms and diplomatic
sanctions against the country in 1992 to pressure it into handing
over two Libyans suspected in the 1988 bombing of a Pam Am flight
over Lockerbie, Scotland.
</P>
<P>
The sanctions include an international flight ban, which Libya
cited in withdrawing from 1994 World Cup qualifying.
</P>
<P>
Italian League leader Inter Milan will be without several
starters, who will be playing World Cup qualifying matches with
their national teams.
</P>
<P>
Twin quakes Sept. 26 killed 10 people in central Italy and
severely damaged the basilica of St. Francis in Assisi. 
</P>
