<HEADLINE> Panama's Earns More From Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, October 7 (Xinhua) -- The Panama Institute of
Tourism reported today that tourism revenues increased 9 percent
during the first nine months.
</P>
<P>
Juan Stanziola, from the statistics department of the Tourism
Institute, said the increase represents 25 million U.S. dollars
above 1996 gains.
</P>
<P>
Stanziola said his country earned 443 million dollars from
tourism-related activities last year, a figure that is expected to
rise to above 460 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
He said Panama's tourism services will benefit from the recent
increase in foreign visitors.
</P>
<P>
The Tourism Exhibition 97, to be held in Panama City from
October 8-11 in the Atlalpa Conventions Center, will also help
boost tourism, he said.
</P>
<P>
Some 250 representatives from tourism companies over the world
will take part in the international event. 
</P>
</TEXT>
