<HEADLINE> Pak, British FM Hold Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's Foreign Minister
Gohar Ayub Khan held talks yesterday with visiting British Foreign
Secretary Robin Cook on international as well as bilateral issues
of mutual interest.
</P>
<P>
They exchanged views on the conflict in Afghanistan and agreed
that immediate return of peace and stability in that country was
essential for the stability in the region, according to sources
from the Foreign Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The two also exchanged views on the Commonwealth summit to be
held this month.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that Ayub Khan briefed his British counterpart
on the latest development in Pak-India relations with special
reference to Jammu and Kashmir.  
</P>
</TEXT>
