<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Township Industry Booming in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, October 8 (Xinhua) -- The output value of the
township enterprises and township industrial businesses of east
China's Jiangxi Province recorded a year-on-year increase of 45
percent each in the first half of the year.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, more than 20 percent of the
rural per capita income was generated from township enterprises in
the first half of the year, and the rural per capita income had an
11.9 percent growth over the same period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
Local officials attributed the growth to the provincial
government's efforts to develop township industrial zones.
</P>
<P>
The government encourages the building of township industrial
zones in the outskirts of towns with good water and power supply,
transportation, and communications. It also places importance on
creating better investment climate for these industrial zones.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, the 267 township industrial zones in
Jiangxi realized an output value totaling 17 billion yuan, with
pre-tax profits of 1.8 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The growth of township industrial zones has strongly backed the
economic development of small towns, a local official said.
</P>
</TEXT>
