<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pippen Takes Surgery on Left Foot </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Scottie Pippen, super star
for the National Basketball Association reigning champions
Chicago, will be out of action for two to three months following
surgery on his left foot.
</P>
<P>
The operation, performed on Monday in New York, leaves the
Bulls shorthanded with the club's season opener barely three
weeks away.
</P>
<P>
Surgery was performed by team orthopaedic surgeon Michael Lewis
on the second-largest toe of Pippen's left foot.
</P>
<P>
"We're sorry to lose Scottie," Bulls general manager Jerry
Krause said. "We're going to lose him for the next two months, at
least. It's going to be a two to three month thing." 
</P>
</TEXT>
