<HEADLINE> Tibet Reports Increased Insurance Premiums </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Tibetan farmers, who formerly paid
lamas for chanting sutras during natural disasters, are now
relying on insurance companies to pay compensation.
</P>
<P>
The region reported a total of 16.3 million yuan in property
insurance premiums paid during the first five months of this year,
up 20 percent on 1996 same period. By the end of September, the
total life insurance premiums had jumped to five million yuan from
a million yuan for 1996.
</P>
<P>
Informed sources say that 1,130 enterprises have purchased
property insurance along with some 11,000 families.  
</P>
</TEXT>
