<HEADLINE> Fernandez Ousts Huber in Filderstadt WTA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bonn, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Mary Joe Fernandez of the United
States upset two-time champion Anke Huber of Germany 6-4, 6-4
Tuesday in a first round match at the 450,000 U.S, dollars WTA
tennis tournament in Filderstadt, Germany.
</P>
<P>
Huber, who won the title in 1991 and 1994 and was a finalist
last year, fought hard in the one hour 23 minutes match, taking
both sets to 4-4, but wasn't enough to overwhelm the powerful
baseline play of Fernandez.
</P>
<P>
Fernandez will next play Naoko Sawamatsu of Japan, who
dispatched Sabine Appelmans of Belgium on Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
