<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Annan Corrects Congo Radio Reports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, October 7 (Xinhua) -- The U.N. head issued a
statement here today, trying to clarify an accusation of the
United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees UNHCR by the radio
of the Democratic Republic of the Congo.
</P>
<P>
Kofi Annan, the Secretary General, said that he deplored the
radio and television broadcasts in the east of the Democratic
Republic of the Congo which "falsely accused" the UNHCR of arming
Rwandan refugees.
</P>
<P>
UNHCR has a consistent policy of humanitarian action around the
world, he said. "It has never been involved in the provision or
supply of arms to any refugee groups," he added.
</P>
<P>
"The charges are completely without foundation. I reiterate my
full confidence in the High Commissioner and in UNHCR staff in the
region, who have performed with great courage and distinction in
extremely difficult circumstances," he said.
</P>
<P>
"I call upon those who are behind this unfounded anti-UNHCR
media campaign to cease their false accusations, which could have
a serious effect on the work and well-being of innocent
humanitarian workers in the region," Annan said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
