<DOCNO> XIE19971008.0326 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Bank Supports Tanzania Human Resources Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 7 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today okayed a
20.9 million U.S. dollar credit for the human resources
development pilot project in Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
The project is designed to increase investment in human capital
to raise incomes, reduce inequality, and improve non-market
outcomes.
</P>
<P>
The project is also aimed at improving Tanzania's education
sector by raising enrollments and quality of primary education,
expanding educational opportunities for poorer girls, building
capacity at the district and community levels as well as upgrading
policy development, planning and research in the education sector.
</P>
<P>
The World Bank financing will be channeled through the
International Development Association (IDA), the Bank's
concessionary lending arm for developing countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
