<HEADLINE> Dow Moves Further Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, October 7 (Xinhua) -- The Dow's slow recovery from
August pulled the index closer to its record high today while
broader stock indexes set more record highs.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average rose 78.09 points to 8,178.31.
It is now only about 80 points from its August 6 peak of 8,259.31.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 5-to-4 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with NYSE volume totaling 551.41
million shares as against 494.85 million in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
Other popular stock measures padded Monday's record highs as
interest rates sank to 6.24 percent, the lowest level since
February 16, 1996.
</P>
<P>
The S&AMP;P 500 rose 10.42 to 983.11, the NYSE composite rose 4.51
to 514.21, and Nasdaq composite rose 15.10 to 1,737.01.
</P>
<P>
The Russell 2000 rose 2.08 to 463.78 for its 24th record close
in 29 sessions, and the American Stock Exchange composite rose
5.10 to 721.90.  
</P>
</TEXT>
